name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info: This is a clinic for the single dose of the Johnson & Johnson COVID-19 vaccine being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older from 12pm until mall closing.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a walk-in clinic at Plum Street YMCA, 505 Plum Street SE, Olympia WA, 98501 from 9am - 1pm. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with warm layers. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: North Fork Brewery
info:
Mobile Vaccine Clinic at North Fork Brewery. Walk-ins welcome. 
After your vaccination, enjoy an on-the-house draft beer or root beer at the brewery! 
Vaccine is free.
Offering Moderna first or second doses.  Bring your card for second doses.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakima Community Vaccine Center
info: ***PFIZER VACCINATIONS*** !!!!VACUNAS DE PFIZER!!! Enter fairgrounds through Gate 15 off of Pacific Avenue.
